cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.DL, cs.SD, cs.CY 

The paper discusses the use of clickstream and pageviews data in constructing the Google matrix for Wikipedia articles, which is a topic related to social impact and information retrieval. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves data analysis and manipulation, which falls under cs.DL (Digital Libraries) and cs.SD (Software Development). Finally, the paper also discusses the use of multilingual measures, which could be relevant to cs.CY (Computers and Society).
